 the bigger picture to just fall off the canvas.', 5662, 0), (249312, 'Seize every opportunity and make it great.', 2878, 0), (249313, 'You are special individual.Nobody can be you.You can rise to a greater heights.', 2878, 0), (249314, 'The power of greatness lies within each of us.', 2878, 0), (249315, 'There is greatness in everyone.Look within yourself and discover your greatness.', 2878, 0), (249316, 'Some achieve greatness through people who lift them higher. Others find it when they have to stand alone.', 27167, 0), (249317, 'There is a divine grace available for you to accomplish far greater things than you could ever imagine nor dream of.', 2878, 0), (249318, 'Besides God, there is no glory above coming from humble beginnings, from sleeping under a porous grass thatched mud hut to rising above and beyond tabernacles of greatness', 43371, 0), (249319, 'When we commit our lives to the Lord,He lives in us, He gives us grace and power to accomplish far greater things.', 2878, 0), (249320, 'You are not as great or terrible as you think you are. Neither are they.', 43372, 0), (249321, 'Greatness rarely comes easy.', 43373, 0), (249322, 'I can be all that I can be.Endless opportunities, this is my world.', 2878, 0), (249323, 'Be great, dwell on great thoughts.', 2878, 0), (249324, 'I''ve many reasons why I believe that every individual I meet is a greatness material', 43374, 0), (249325, 'Believe you are great and you will be great.', 2878, 0), (249326, 'If you refuse to accept nothing but the best you will often get it.', 27144, 0), (249327, 'Don''t give-up on your greatest masterpiece — you.', 7223, 0), (249328, 'All great men face challenges in the pursuit of their goals. However, the challenges did not deter them for pushing forward and realizing their goals.', 2878, 0), (249329, 'Remember that any desire is tested; the greater the desire, the greater the tests.', 7223, 0), (249330, 'Greatness does not approach him who is forever looking down". My eyes are seeing through what the ordinary men call a mirage!', 29933, 0), (249331, 'Well, in war, you can only be killed once. But in politics, many times.', 1150, 0), (249332, 'The greatest self is a peaceful smile, that always sees the world smiling back.', 7223, 0), (249333, 'The grandeur of the thieving falsity is larceny, the fall of cities.', 10831, 0), (249334, 'Every shortcut has a price usually greater than the reward.', 7223, 0), (249335, 'Source truth exists in greater abundance outside of the symbolic system of words.', 7223, 0), (249336, 'If you don''t believe in God, then the God concept is a great placeholder for everything we don''t know, which is exponentially more than we do know.', 7223, 0), (249337, 'You are likely the greatest obstacle to achieving your own dreams.', 7223, 0), (249338, 'God''s help is available for us to achieve great things. We must put our hope and trust in the Lord.', 2878, 0), (249339, 'When you live positively it is impossible to not also be living for something greater than yourself.', 7223, 0), (249340, 'Hopefully and devoutly focus on your greater possibilities.', 7223, 0), (249341, 'When you hand good people possibility, they do great things.', 11199, 0), (249342, 'When your absence is felt, your presence is the essence and it makes a difference.', 332, 0), (249343, 'If you live with values for yourself, then you become of great value to all who know you.', 7223, 0), (249344, 'Between goal and success, there is one critical thing - perseverance: it is the fundamental belief to always succeed, the determination to turn goal to gold, the greatness to never give up, the foresight to dream that enables you to make it happen.', 3337, 0), (249345, 'All my life I have refused to be for or against parties, for or against nations, for or against people. I never seek novelty or the eccentric; I do not go from land to land to contrast civilizations. I seek only, wherever I go, for symbols of greatness, and as I have already said, they may be found in the eyes of a child, in the movement of a gladiator, in the heart of a gypsy, in twilight in Ireland or in moonrise over the deserts. To hold the spirit of greatness is in my mind what the world was created for. The human body is beautiful as this spirit shines through, and art is great as it translates and embodies this spirit.', 19737, 0), (249346, 'If you were really humble you would be great, because humility would never squander the magnificent gift of life.', 7223, 0), (249347, 'Live in this moment because this moment is the only thing that''s real and the only time that you can create greatness.', 25535, 0), (249348, 'We knew she [Sylvia] was unusual, because of the seriousness with which she was treated, the lofty importance of her job as guest managing editor, and because she was kept fast at her desk when the rest of us were allowed to fool around….I remember we discussed how the editors treater her differently from the rest of us, as if she had been pre-recognized as someone they were expecting great things of.', 25226, 0), (249349, 'I feel the magic between you and I', 43375, 0), (249350, 'Within you, within all human beings, is a seed of greatness that makes their kind quake with fear.', 6722, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (249351, 'Your greater purpose is already written in the fabric of your being', 43376, 0), (249352, 'You need not strive to become your greater purpose.', 7223, 0), (249353, 'There is no greater path than the act of listening.', 7223, 0), (249354, 'There is no greater path than the act of listening, because the observer who listens can begin to see themselves as a part of one expression of purpose and beingness.', 7223, 0), (249355, 'To be great at anything that you do, you have to love it! but also give it your all..', 24630, 0), (249356, 'Place Yourself On the Scale You Desire.Don''t Expect Others To Do It For You. It''s An Individual Thing Called SELF-ESTEEM.', 1313, 0), (249357, 'Be Prepared For Life''s Emergencies. Always Arm Yourself With God''s Word.', 1313, 0), (249358, 'Where You Hail From Isn''t As Important As Who You Are and What You Do...Your Doings Define and Describe You.', 1313, 0), (249359, 'God Is Love But For This Love To Be Real To Us Depends Largely On Our Responses and Reactions to Him.', 1313, 0), (249360, 'Think of any great man or woman. How can you separate them from the years in which they lived? You can''t. Their greatness lies in their response to that moment.', 5949, 0), (249361, 'I believe...that to be very poor and very beautiful is most probably a moral failure more than an artistic success. Shakespeare would have done well in any generation because he would have refused to die in a corner; he would have taken the false gods and made them over; he would have taken the current formulae and forced them into something lesser men thought them incapable of. Alive today he would undoubtedly have written and directed motion pictures, plays, and God knows what. Instead of saying, "This medium is not good," he would have used it and made it good. If some people called some his work cheap (which some of it was), he wouldn''t have cared a rap, because he would know that without some vulgarity there is no complete man. He would have hated refinement, as such, because it is always a withdrawal, and he was too tough to shrink from anything.', 1016, 0), (249362, 'It is usually the roughest road that leads to the heights of greatness.', 11230, 0), (249363, 'To write about him is to write about Greatness. To discuss him is todiscuss Intellectual Brilliance. To think of him is to think of Modesty,Simplicity and Lucidity. To remember him is to remember Nationalism atits finest hour. He was not one of those who merely achieved greatnessnor certainly one of those upon whom greatness was thrust-he was infact born great.', 24895, 0), (249364, 'But at the same time, there must never be the least hesitation in giving up a position the moment it is shown to be untenable. It is not going too far to say that the greatness of a scientific investigator does not rest on the fact of his having never made a mistake, but rather on his readiness to admit that he has done so, whenever the contrary evidence is cogent enough.', 43377, 0), (249365, 'Always give your best', 43378, 0), (249366, 'To achieve great things, we must live as though we were never going to die.', 25680, 0), (249367, 'Nothing great is ever achieved without enthusiasm, passion and love. Not professionally or personally. We will not find greatness in our jobs, in our marriages, our children, in our friendships, nor in our spiritual growth without these three key elements. ~ Jason Versey', 15661, 0), (249368, 'It is never an idea, technology, market forces, or access to capital that makes a company innovative. What differentiates an innovative company from an average company is the people working inside the company.', 15049, 0), (249369, 'No matter how full one''s head might be with the image of greatness, one was useless, I found out, unless one was a worthy man first.', 3223, 0), (249370, 'He who loved himself became great in himself, and he who loved others became great through his devotion, but he who loved God became greater than all.', 1027, 0), (249371, 'That moment when this heart.. stops.. almost as if it never existed.When every.. breathe.. slows down.. almost as if you never ... needed as single breathe of airWhen time stops.. almost as if every second never mattered.In that moment... I''m infinite.In that moment... I am immortal.In that moment... I am Finally alive.', 23314, 0), (249372, 'Virtue is excellence, something uncommonly great and beautiful, which rises far above what is vulgar and ordinary.', 2485, 0), (249373, 'She wanted to be remembered for doing something great. And her greatest fear was of being completely forgotten.', 19459, 0), (249374, 'You''re a great man, but only when seen from afar.', 2418, 0), (249375, 'I told you it would be difficult! If I were you I would just not bother trying these tasks! They are great challenges, clearly too great for you.” said Guya, but there was a certain sparkle in his eye as he said it. “I shall complete your tasks, ” said Yoshiko firmly. “And I’ll be back sooner than you think!” With that he spread his wings to head for Fire School. “Oh and one more thing Guya” Yoshiko added. Perhaps when I return you will be so kind as to stop calling me a little dragon!” As Yoshiko flew off Guya chuckled to himself.', 43379, 0), (249376, 'Those who truly want greatness must surround themselves with people even greater than they are.', 645, 0), (249377, 'That men, who might have tower''d in the vanOf all the congregated world, to fanAnd winnow from the coming step of timeAll chaff of custom, wipe away all slimeLeft by men-slugs and human serpentry,Have been content to let occasion die,Whilst they did sleep in love''s Elysium.', 191, 0), (249378, 'Back then: to be regarded as well-known, one had to be great. Today: to be regarded as great, one has to be well-known.', 4616, 0), (249379, 'No, I don''t admire the genius. But I admire and love the result of the genius''s activity in the world, of which the great man is only the poor necessary tool, only, so to speak, the paltry awl to bore with.', 7861, 0), (249380, 'He was simply and staunchly true to his duty alike in the large case and in the small. So all true souls ever are. So every true soul ever was, ever is, and ever will be. There is nothing little to the really great in spirit.', 96, 0), (249381, 'But if modesty is interpreted not as diffidence or self-effacingness, but as non-overweening, a realistic assessment of the job to be done and one''s ability to do it, then you might say the chief virtue of excellent artists is their modesty...But knowing your limits and going to them isn''t arrogance. It''s greatness of spirit.', 77, 0), (249382, 'Most rules are made by people with no authority who want to control and limit you from reaching your true potential. Ignore them, break their rules, and wave at them as you soar past them to greatness.', 645, 0), (249383, 'The great works are produced in such an ecstasy of love that they must always be unworthy of it, however great their worth otherwise.', 11, 0), (249384, 'A surrendered heart leads to greatness. A stubborn heart leads to struggle.', 4406, 0), (249385, 'There is a scene in one of the Rocky movies where after the match Apollo Creed and Rocky are waiting for the scoring of their brawl all beat up and battered, obviously both fighters gave all they had to win, and Apollo Creed says to Rocky - "Your not getting a rematch" and Rocky says "I don''t want one".I love that scene. That''s when you know that you left no doubt - that your opponent, win or lose, never wants to compete against you ever again. That''s fighting.', 29957, 0), (249386, 'There will never be "the right time" in your life to do a great thing. You must create that time and greatness will follow.', 29957, 0), (249387, 'The world offers you comfort. But you were not made for comfort. You were made for greatness', 856, 0), (249388, 'Ten years from now, no one is going to care how quickly the books came out. The only thing that will matter, the only thing anyone will remember, is how good they were. That''s my main concern, and always will be.', 169, 0), (249389, 'Expression is saying what you wish to say, Impression is saying what others wish to hear.', 38764, 0), (249390, 'Our success will not come from the acts of our forefathers, but can come alone from what we are doing now. Those who have inherited rich blood can use that richness in building greatness in themselves, but those who have not the privilege of such inheritance need not be discouraged. They can create their own rich blood and make it as rich as they like.', 41, 0), (249391, 'Get it Right today, for today wil never come again', 26273, 0), (249392, 'When you have nothing to say, don''t.', 38764, 0), (249393, 'True greatness demands humility', 43380, 0), (249394, 'He was searching for something greater, if there is a thing greater than love, and he could not settle until he found it.', 32121, 0), (249395, 'What’s that around your neck?” asked Emily. “It’s a golden star.” Said Reed.“What did you get it for?”“Chemistry class.”“What’s the star for?” the shadow asked, Usually stars represent a straight A student. “You get it for having greatness. But Emily doesn’t know what that is.” He said, answering the shadows question and looking at Emily. “Greatness, what’s greatness?” Emily asked, all wide eyed, and clueless looking“It’s when you do really awesome stuff, and people recognize you for it.”“Oh, no” Emily laughed .”No, I don’t know what that is.', 40445, 0), (249396, 'Describing Robert Bunsen:As an investigator he was great, as a teacher he was greater, as a man and friend he was greatest.', 43381, 0), (249397, 'Greatness is achieved, not only by doing great things, but also,by making the small things we dogreat.', 26379, 0), (249398, 'Life is a beautiful dream to be cherished, as long as it lasts.', 38764, 0), (249399, 'Every one is fond of comparing himself to something great and grandiose, as Louis XIV likened himself to the sun, and others have had like similes. I am more humble. I am a mere street scavenger (chiffonier) of science. With my hook in my hand and my basket on my back, I go about the streets of science, collecting what I find.', 43382, 0), (249400, 'Emil Fischer represents a symbol of Germany''s greatness.', 43383, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (249401, 'Goodness is richer than greatness. It consists not in the outward things we do, but in the inward thing we are.', 43384, 0), (249402, 'I believe "Leadership" is creating the environment for the greatness in people to emerge.', 11230, 0), (249403, 'Greatness depends on where you are coming from.', 2133, 0), (249404, 'There was never a great genius without a touch of madness.', 29394, 0), (249405, 'You can only exceed your limits if you’ve discovered them.', 29598, 0), (249406, 'Who are you not to be great? You, with the imagination of a brilliant child and the powers of an ancient god. Who are you to be ordinary? You, who can resend life or raise the dead.Who are you to be afraid? You, who can serve as judge and jury while hoarding infinite lives.Who are you to be a slave to the past? You who can travel time like the oceans or rewrite history with a single word.Who are you to be anonymous? You whose names should be spoken in reverend tones or terrified whispers.And who are you to deny greatness? If you would deny it to yourself, you deny it to the entire world. And we will not be denied.', 43385, 0), (249407, 'The root of all true greatness, is humility.', 103, 0), (249408, 'It is surprising how many great men started out as horse thieves.', 43386, 0), (249409, 'Begin where you are and what you are.', 43387, 0), (249410, 'True greatness is often unrecognized.', 43387, 0), (249411, 'The sum of greatest is not asking ''What do I want to be'' but rather ''Who do I want to be', 4406, 0), (249412, 'Some books sold because they are (said to be) great. Some are (said to be) great because they sold.', 4616, 0), (249413, 'Do you ever see a man who struts around altogether too large to notice an ordinary working mechanic? Do you think he is great? He is nothing but a puffed-up balloon, held down by his big feet. There is no greatness there.', 43387, 0), (249414, 'But they also awarded a quite respectable 55th place to Enoch Powell, thereby demonstrating that, for certain sections of the population, being an unpleasant racist constitutes no bar to greatness.', 43388, 0), (249415, 'being different can work for the individual who are comfortable with themselves, and most importantly work hard to achieve greatness.', 6992, 0), (249416, 'Seek and achieve "GREATNESS" instead of mere success', 26591, 0), (249417, 'Tom''s cowardice was as huge as his courage, as it must be in great men.', 1070, 0), (249418, 'Encouraging others can be the catalyst to unleashing their greatness.', 938, 0), (249419, 'I don''t know what kind of great I''m bound to be," Dove considered his prospects calmly, "all I know for certain is I''m born a world-shaker.', 3714, 0), (249420, 'Greatness lies not in high or outstanding ability. It lies simply in the willingness to use what we have for others. The greater the `other people` dimension, the greater our personal `greatness`.', 43389, 0), (249421, 'Success is the understanding, release and maximization of capacity.', 3337, 0), (249422, 'The only permission, the only validation, and the only opinion that matters in our quest for greatness is our own.', 161, 0), (249423, 'Impossible is nothing.', 1751, 0), (249424, 'Greatness consists not in the holding of some future office, but really consists in doing great deeds with little means and the accomplishment of vast purposes from the private ranks of life. To be great at all one must be great here, now, in Philadelphia.', 43387, 0), (249425, 'Let every man or woman here, if you never hear me again, remember this, that if you wish to be great at all, you must begin where you are and with what you are, in Philadelphia, now.', 43387, 0), (249426, 'Greatness is to stay humble when the whole world calls you great!', 3701, 0), (249427, 'Greatness consists not in the holding of some future office, but really consists in doing great deeds with little means and the accomplishment of vast purposes from the private rants of life. To be great at all one must be great here, now, in Philadelphia.', 43387, 0), (249428, 'You have a great name .. They must kill your name before they can kill you , cuz name is your idea , and ideas are bulletproofs :))', 38338, 0), (249429, 'Great men know how to control two things', 43390, 0), (249430, 'Use your hater to make you greater!', 4005, 0), (249431, 'There is an enduring freshness in what remains strange and obscure which the cliches of greatness can only evoke nostalgia for.', 1446, 0), (249432, 'The pursuit of greatness means that laziness has no place in your life.', 2045, 0), (249433, 'In general I strive for greatness and rational achievement, but I admit to you I’ve a terrible fondness for women, a tendency towards drunkenness, and a weakness for the fumes of the poppy—opium and other miserable beauties.', 587, 0), (249434, 'We like to stress the commonness of heroes. Essences seem undemocratic. We feel oppressed by the call to greatness. We regard an interest in glory or perfection as a sign of mental unhealthiness, and have decided that high achievers, who are called overachievers, owe their surplus ambition to a defect in mothering (either too little or too much). We want to admire but think we have a right not to be intimidated. We dislike feeling inferior to an ideal. So away with ideals, with essences. The only ideals allowed are healthy ones -- those everyone may aspire to, or comfortably imagine oneself possessing.', 4673, 0), (249435, 'God in his unending greatness and glory and man in his unending littleness, prepared for the worst but rarely for the best, prepared for the possible but rarely for the impossible.', 899, 0), (249436, 'Only adversity provides the opportunity for greatness.', 38780, 0), (249437, 'Greatness is sifted through the grind, therefore don''t despise the hard work now for surely it will be worth it in the end.', 8163, 0), (249438, 'God is great, God is faithful".~R. Alan Woods [2103]', 4246, 0), (249439, 'Nay, could their numbers countervail the stars,Or ever-drizzling drops of April showers,Or wither''d leaves that autumn shaketh down,Yet would the Soldan by his conquering powerSo scatter and consume them in his rage, That not a man should live to rue their fall.', 6093, 0), (249440, 'For something to be great, there has to be some kind of trial or some type of struggle that actually makes it special or valuable to you. Otherwise, anything could be easily taken for granted.', 1029, 0), (249441, 'A man becomes Mahadev only when he fights for good.', 479, 0), (249442, 'I write because I''m free,because I can,because I will. I write because I must,because I''m breathing,because I''d go crazy otherwise,because it''s who I am.I write to make a statement,to share my thoughts,to discover myself,to express my ideas.But most of all, I write for future generations.I write for love. I write to inspire.I write to encourage. I write for me.', 9855, 0), (249443, 'But what is great can only begin great.', 2500, 0), (249444, 'A man must love a thing very much if he practices it without any hope of fame or money, but even practice it without any hope of doing it well. Such a man must love the toils of the work more than any other man can love the rewards of it.', 263, 0), (249445, 'The real great man is the man who makes every man feel great.', 263, 0), (249446, 'When it is impossible to stretch the very elastic threads of historical ratiocination any farther, when actions are clearly contrary to all that humanity calls right or even just, the historians produce a saving conception of ‘greatness.’ ‘Greatness,’ it seems, excludes the standards of right and wrong. For the ‘great’ man nothing is wrong, there is no atrocity for which a ‘great’ man can be blamed.', 93, 0), (249447, 'The loves and sorrows that are great are destroyed by their own plentitude.', 40, 0), (249448, 'Greatness is in influence, and not necessarily in affluence. It is not achieved by being a ''paper millionaire'', but by being a ''people millionaire''.', 1660, 0), (249449, 'The idea isn''t to do the impossible. The idea is to show the world that if one man can do the impossible, then maybe the rest of the world can do what''s possible.', 43391, 0), (249450, 'Everyone has a calling. Thus, everyone has the chance to do something remarkable that will make hime great in the eyes of others.', 43392, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (249451, 'The great would not think themselves demigods if the little did not worship them.', 38572, 0), (249452, 'Endeavor for greatness, venture for the sake of the heart.', 9855, 0), (249453, 'Everyone has a calling. Thus, everyone has the chance to do something remarkable that will make him great in the eyes of others.', 43393, 0), (249454, 'I think that if I ever have kids, and they are upset, I won''t tell them that people are starving in China or anything like that because it wouldn''t change the fact that they were upset. And even if somebody else has it much worse, that doesn''t really change the fact that you have what you have.', 6, 0), (249455, 'And that''s the thing about people who mean everything they say. They think everyone else does too.', 342, 0), (249456, 'Whoever is careless with the truth in small matters cannot be trusted with important matters', 104, 0), (249457, 'We are all travelers in the wilderness of this world, and the best we can find in our travels is an honest friend.', 449, 0), (249458, 'Freethinkers are those who are willing to use their minds without prejudice and without fearing to understand things that clash with their own customs, privileges, or beliefs. This state of mind is not common, but it is essential for right thinking...', 93, 0), (249459, 'You wear a mask for so long, you forget who you were beneath it.', 1001, 0), (249460, 'To conceal anything from those to whom I am attached, is not in my nature. I can never close my lips where I have opened my heart.', 96, 0), (249461, 'Nothing in this world is harder than speaking the truth, nothing easier than flattery.', 57, 0), (249462, 'Anything is better than lies and deceit!', 93, 0), (249463, 'Living with integrity means: Not settling for less than what you know you deserve in your relationships. Asking for what you want and need from others. Speaking your truth, even though it might create conflict or tension. Behaving in ways that are in harmony with your personal values. Making choices based on what you believe, and not what others believe.', 28913, 0), (249464, 'You ask me what forces me to speak? a strange thing', 43394, 0), (249465, 'If you want to write a negative review, don''t tickle me gently with your aesthetic displeasure about my work. Unleash the goddamn Kr', 2295, 0), (249466, 'Honest people don''t hide their deeds.', 55, 0), (249467, 'The answer is good things only happen to you if you''re good. Good? Honest is more what I mean... Be anything but a coward, a pretender, an emotional crook, a whore: I''d rather have cancer than a dishonest heart.', 262, 0), (249468, 'if you wanted to do something absolutely honest, something true, it always turned out to be a thing that had to be done alone.', 3259, 0), (249469, 'If we are not ashamed to think it, we should not be ashamed to say it.', 1306, 0), (249470, 'Integrity is telling myself the truth. And honesty is telling the truth to other people.', 11183, 0), (249471, 'Can you honestly love a dishonest thing?', 1070, 0), (249472, 'I meant what I said and I said what I meant.', 3, 0), (249473, 'NO reader has ANY obligation to an author, whether it be to leave a review or to write a "constructive" one. I put out a product. You are consumers of that product. Since when does that mean you have to kiss my ass? Hey, I like Pop-Tarts and eat them a few times a year; since when does that mean I''m obligated to support Kellogg''s in any way except legally purchasing the Pop-Tarts before I eat them? I wasn''t aware that purchasing and consuming a product meant I was under some sort of fucking thrall in which I''m only allowed to either praise the Pop-Tart (which to be honest isn''t hard, especially the S''mores flavor) or, if I am going to criticize a flavor, offer a specific and detailed analysis as to why, phrased in as inoffensive and gentle a manner as possible so as not to upset the gentle people at Kello', 3282, 0), (249474, 'There''s one way to find out if a man is honest: ask him; if he says yes, you know he''s crooked.', 286, 0), (249475, 'All cruel people describe themselves as paragons of frankness.', 355, 0), (249476, 'Am I glowing?""Like a Christmas tree.""Not just the star?"The bed moved a little, and I felt his hand brush my arm. "No. You''re super bright. It''s kind of like looking at the sun.', 366, 0), (249477, 'Honesty is a very expensive gift, Don''t expect it from cheap people.', 6410, 0), (249478, 'Honesty is more than not lying. It is truth telling, truth speaking, truth living, and truth loving.', 9153, 0), (249479, 'The best men tell you the truth because they think you can take it; the worst men either try to preserve you in some innocent state with their false protection, or are ‘brutally honest.’ When someone tells, lets you think for yourself, experience your own emotions, he is treating you as a true equal, a friend…And the best men cook for you.', 213, 0), (249480, 'Do not consider me now as an elegant female intending to plague you, but as a rational creature speaking the truth from her heart.', 24, 0), (249481, 'Unless you''re ashamed of yourself now and then, you''re not honest', 344, 0), (249482, 'All the other children at my school are stupid. Except I''m not meant to call them stupid, even though this is what they are.', 1066, 0), (249483, 'Nothing is so difficult as not deceiving oneself.', 1163, 0), (249484, 'If someone doesn''t value evidence, what evidence are you going to provide to prove that they should value it? If someone doesn’t value logic, what logical argument could you provide to show the importance of logic?', 1816, 0), (249485, 'To be honest, as this world goes, is to be one man picked out of ten thousand.', 13, 0), (249486, 'The trouble with most of us is that we''d rather be ruined by praise than saved by criticism.', 1699, 0), (249487, 'No legacy is so rich as honesty.', 13, 0), (249488, 'The only time you seem honest is when you’re insulting someone!”“The only honest things I can say to you are insults.', 508, 0), (249489, 'Yeah, it never fails to amaze me how a single lie can undo an entire lifetime of good. (Aiden)', 226, 0), (249490, 'The whole art of government consists in the art of being honest.', 1207, 0), (249491, 'Never separate the life you lead from the words you speak.', 43395, 0), (249492, 'No man means all he says, and yet very few say all they mean, for words are slippery and thought is viscous.', 2796, 0), (249493, 'Cynic, n. A blackguard whose faulty vision sees things as they are not as they ought to be.', 224, 0), (249494, 'Honesty: The best of all the lost arts.', 286, 0), (249495, 'Speak what you think today in hard words and tomorrow speak what tomorrow thinks in hard words again, though it contradict every thing you said today.', 760, 0), (249496, 'I’m a liar and a cheat and a coward, but I will never, ever, let a friend down. Unless of course not letting them down requires honesty, fair play, or bravery.', 2417, 0), (249497, 'To be truly positive in the eyes of some, you have to risk appearing negative in the eyes of others.', 230, 0), (249498, 'She wanted to cause him pain for taking a place in her heart she wouldn''t have given him if she''d known the truth.', 371, 0), (249499, 'The truth needs so little rehearsal.', 679, 0), (249500, 'When you find that people are not telling you the truth---look out!', 94, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (249501, 'Nothing is more intolerable than to have admit to yourself your own errors.', 1791, 0), (249502, 'And I said, ''That last thing is what you can''t get, Carlo. Nobody can get to that last thing. We keep on living in hopes of catching it once and for all.', 382, 0), (249503, 'When we turn around & come face to face with our destiny, we discover that words (spoken) are not enough. I know so many people who are brilliant speakers but are quite incapable of practising what they preach. It''s one thing to describe a situation & quite another to experience it. I realised a long time ago that a warrior in search of his dream must take his inspiration from what he actually does & not from what he imagines himself doing.', 34, 0), (249504, 'What you didn''t tell someone was just as debilitating as what you did.', 21, 0), (249505, 'Being nice merely to be liked in return nullifies the point.', 230, 0), (249506, 'Though I am not naturally honest, I am sometimes so by chance.', 13, 0), (249507, 'Never esteem anything as of advantage to you that will make you break your word or lose your self-respect.', 267, 0), (249508, 'You cannot con an honest man.', 674, 0), (249509, 'There are honest people in the world, but only because the devil considers their asking prices ridiculous.', 610, 0), (249510, 'Honesty is always good, except when it''s better to lie. ', 285, 0), (249511, 'Just tell yourself a story that''ll satisfy you and pretend he told it.', 828, 0), (249512, 'I would rather be damned by my honesty, than caged by my lies.', 43396, 0), (249513, 'Honesty was a tough customer... Once you started allowing yourself some honesty, it couldn''t easily be contained or limited to one part of your life. It was like poison ivy or a bossy houseguest. Once it was there, you couldn''t tell it what to do. You had to really fight to keep it from taking over. ', 256, 0), (249514, 'Honest differences are often a healthy sign 